Observation Details: Photographed and Recorded - I moved this exhausted bird off of the road

Vocalizing along marsh side of main park road at “speed 20 ahead” sign .25 km south of entrance gate. Golden hood with beady eye, needle-like black bill. Unmarked golden yellow beneath from throat to belly, unmarked white vent. Plain blue grey wings & tail, latter with subterminal white spots. Heard this bird from the car the day I arrived (9th) & didn’t think it sounded like a CARW!
